result.name: Hup Seng

reviews.text: On the expensive side. Quality is fine.
Offering traditional Chinese chiu chow style desserts at affordable prices.

Super nice dessert also known as tong sui. I love their 雷沙湯圓, so fresh and still hot while you eating. Thanks to my HK friend who bring us to have this delicious local tong sui. The tong sui not so sweet and it really taste good. My HK friend recommended us to take 潮州綠豆邊清心丸, quite nice. My mom as usual took 番薯糖水, the soup really spicy because of ginger. Taste yummy too. We went there again on our last day in HK, we have ordered 紅豆蛋 and the other one is 蓮子蛋. The eggs really nice and fresh. One of my favourite tong sui is red bean soup and i really love it coz it's not sweet and very smooth. I'm gonna miss this tong sui place. I will be back again for my next visit.
Must try Chinese sweet soup desert
Amazing quality and service. A very traditional HK style desert spot. Must try in HK.

result.name: Chiu Chow Hop Shing Dessert

reviews.text: Great stuffs - in an old-fashioned kind of way.
Local traditional dessert. The desserts are really good and not overly sweet. The desserts are about 50hkd each.

This old dessert place really stood out more when new dessert places hardly use the traditional ingredients for dessert anymore. If you come to have dinner in Kowloon city, do leave some space in your stomach for the dessert here!
traditional and nice
Local dessert place.
